        "type": "text",
        "content": "A 20‑bus power system model consistent with the paper's 2035 Scottish wind curtailment case was successfully built. The model allocates a total of 50 GW onshore wind in Scotland (5 buses × 10 GW/bus), places the main load in England, and sets the capacity of each of the five Scotland‑England boundary links to 1500 MW, accurately replicating the transmission bottleneck scenario described in the original paper.",
        "path": null,
