            "Boundary Transmission Constraints: Each of the five Scotland‑England links has a capacity of 1500 MW, giving a total transfer capability of only 7.5 GW, which creates a significant bottleneck relative to the 50 GW wind capacity, exactly reproducing the constraint settings in the paper."
