        "type": "text",
        "content": "By performing linear optimal power flow under two scenarios (with and without network constraints), the critical impact of network constraints on wind curtailment was quantified. Under the constrained scenario, the total wind curtailment over 168 hours reached 45.94%, closely matching the paper's 44.5%. In the unconstrained scenario, with unlimited transmission capacity, all wind was utilised, giving a curtailment rate of 0.00%, which conversely confirms the dominant role of constraints.",
